Product description

22-in-1 Multi-Outlet - Power Strip Surge Protector

Our brand provides safe and smart energy solutions based on innovation, reliability and quality.

We aim to be a leader in the energy industry, helping our customers achieve a smarter, safer lifestyle through continuous innovation and excellence.

This incredible power tower contains a 2300J internal surge protector that will automatically shut down in the event of an overwhelming surge (spike/lightning). The overload protector also closes in the event of overheating, overcurrent or short circuit. All you have to do is press the reset switch on the side to turn it back on!

  • Lightning Strike Protection
  • Automatic Power-off Protection
  • Short Circuit Protection
  • Overheating Protection
  • Overload Protection


Wide spacing for large adapters

We've made sure there's plenty of room for your socket extensions, so you can easily insert them without any hassle.


45° Flat Plug Power Strip

Flat designs are compact and can be concealed behind furniture. The 45° plug does not block the socket below.


Fire resistant material

This product is made of 1382°F heat-retardant ABS+PC material, which effectively prevents your power strip from becoming a fire source.

Q&A

Q1: Does this power tower strip have a waranty？

A1: Sure, this product is covered by a 1-year waranty. And our 24-hours customer support will back you through any problems with our product.

Q2: How does the power tower keep my electronics safe?

A2: There is an overload protector on the bottom, if the total current of the AC outlets exceeds 15A, the overload protector will be triggered to protect your valuable devices.

Q3: Is this power tower strip a surge protector?

A3: Yes, its surge protection is rated 2300J to protect your attached devices from voltage or current fluctuations.

Q4: What's the cable length of this surge protector tower?

A4: 6 FT. 16AWG heavy-duty power cable and top-grade heat retardant casing adopted to avoid heat and fire.

    The product looks and feels high-quality, but only time will tell how reliable it is.
    Positive features:
    - Compact, takes up little space.
    - Sturdy, stays in place even when loaded with cables and adapters (could be heavier at the bottom for added stability).
    - Very conveniently spaced and oriented sockets, allows both plugs and adapters to be connected (larger adapters would fit if connected interchangeably with plugs, e.g. plug-adapter-plug-adapter).
    - Total of 16 three-prong outlets.
    - Power on/off switches, two groups (8 receptacles each), allow all connected devices in each group to be turned off (efficient for simultaneously disconnecting power adapters and stand-by devices for safety and energy savings).
    - Power on/off indicators, visual control of what is currently powered.
    - Three USB-A and two USB-C ports for charging.
    - Overload protection switch (good sign of a professionally designed product, nice to have, but I doubt you'll ever need it unless you start connecting electric kettles and irons along with regular electronic devices). According to the data sheet, the unit is rated at 2 kW at 125 V, a normal load for a US duplex 16-A wall outlet.
    So far, only one negative feature:
    - Access to the power buttons (especially the one on the back) can be obstructed by the attached plugs and adapters. You can still reach them, but with some difficulty, depending on what is connected around them. The manufacturer should have thought about placing these buttons on the top, which is completely empty.
    What I have connected to the tower: two laptops, two 24-in displays, 250-W docking station, two designer's desktop work lamps, two external hard drives.
